  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "the handy `./tests/scripts/minikube.sh` script does not specify that minikube should use RBAC when it starts up minikube: https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/master/tests/scripts/minikube.sh#L58\r\n\r\nIt's useful to always be running with RBAC on so that we can catch any permissions regressions, new required permissions for new code, etc.\r\n\r\nI thought this would be a simple fix to just pass `--extra-config=apiserver.Authorization.Mode=RBAC` as per https://github.com/kubernetes/minikube/blob/master/docs/configuring_kubernetes.md#examples.  This seems to work OK for Rook, but `kube-dns` is in a crash loop:\r\n```\r\n> kubectl -n kube-system get pod -l k8s-app=kube-dns\r\nNAME                       READY     STATUS             RESTARTS   AGE\r\nkube-dns-910330662-ccc9m   2/3       CrashLoopBackOff   53         2h\r\n```\r\n\r\nkubedns logs show that it's missing RBAC permissions:\r\n```\r\n> kubectl -n kube-system logs -lk8s-app=kube-dns -c kubedns\r\nE0819 00:25:59.762761       1 reflector.go:199] k8s.io/dns/vendor/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go:94: Failed to list *v1.Endpoints: User \"system:serviceaccount:kube-system:default\" cannot list endpoints at the cluster scope. (get endpoints)\r\nE0819 00:25:59.762857       1 reflector.go:199] k8s.io/dns/vendor/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go:94: Failed to list *v1.Service: User \"system:serviceaccount:kube-system:default\" cannot list services at the cluster scope. (get services)\r\nE0819 00:25:59.763025       1 reflector.go:199] k8s.io/dns/vendor/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go:94: Failed to list *v1.ConfigMap: User \"system:serviceaccount:kube-system:default\" cannot list configmaps in the namespace \"kube-system\". (get configmaps)\r\n```",
  "closed_at": "2017-10-24T22:02:13Z",
